goals.visualization: Bar chart of Gram Staining vs Count of Bacteria
goals.rationale: This helps in understanding the proportion of bacteria that are Gram-positive or Gram-negative.

goals.question: What is the correlation between Penicillin and Streptomycin?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of Penicillin vs Streptomycin
goals.rationale: This helps in understanding if there is any relationship between the effectiveness of Penicillin and Streptomycin against bacteria.

goals.question: What is the distribution of Neomycin effectiveness across different genera of bacteria?
goals.visualization: Box plot of Neomycin vs Genus
goals.rationale: This helps in understanding if there are any genera of bacteria that are more susceptible or resistant to Neomycin.

goals.question: What is the overall effectiveness of Penicillin, Streptomycin and Neomycin against all bacteria?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of Penicillin, Streptomycin and Neomycin vs Count of Bacteria
goals.rationale: This helps in understanding the relative effectiveness of the three antibiotics against all bacteria.

goals.question: What is the distribution of Streptomycin effectiveness across different Gram Staining categories?
goals.visualization: Box plot of Streptomycin vs Gram Staining
goals.rationale: This helps in understanding if there are any differences in the effectiveness of Streptomycin against Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gram_staining_counts = data['Gram_Staining'].value_counts()
    ax = gram_staining_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bacteria based on their Gram Staining?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Gram Staining')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Bacteria')
    ax.legend(gram_staining_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Penicillin'], data['Streptomycin'], c=data['Gram_Staining'].astype('category').cat.codes, cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Penicillin')
    plt.ylabel('Streptomycin')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between Penicillin and Streptomycin?', wrap=True)
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Gram_Staining")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='Genus', y='Neomycin', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Neomycin effectiveness across different genera of bacteria?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Genus')
    plt.ylabel('Neomycin')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('Genus').sum()[['Penicillin', 'Streptomycin', 'Neomycin']]
    ax = data_grouped.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('What is the overall effectiveness of Penicillin, Streptomycin and Neomycin against all bacteria?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Genus')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Bacteria')
    plt.legend(title='Antibiotics')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='Streptomycin', by='Gram_Staining', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Streptomycin effectiveness across different Gram Staining categories?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Gram Staining')
    ax.set_ylabel('Streptomycin')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
